  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN181.1-kilavi">iṭaiccurat toḻiyak karutiya neñciṟkuc <app><lem>colliyatu</lem><rdg wit="#C5">talaimakaṉ kūṟṟu</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What was said to the heart that intended to stay behind in the middle of the desert.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN181.1">
        <l>tuṉṉaruṅ kāṉamun tuṇita lāṟṟāy</l>
        <l>piṉṉiṉṟu peyarac cūḻntaṉai yāyi</l>
        <l>ṉeṉṉilai yuraimō neñcē yoṉṉā</l>
        <l>rō<supplied>m</supplied>pa<supplied>ra</supplied>ṇ kaṭanta vīṅkuperun tāṉai</l>
        <l>yaṭupōr <supplied>miñi</supplied>li ceruvēl kaṭaii</l>
        <l>muru<supplied>ku</supplied>ṟaḻ muṉpoṭu porukaḷañ civappa</l>
        <l>vaṇmai yeyiṉaṉ <supplied>vī</supplied>ḻn<supplied>te</supplied>ṉa ñāyiṟ</l>
        <l>ṟoṇkati ruruvam putaiya vōrāṅku</l>
        <l>vampap puḷḷiṉ kampalaip peruntōṭu</l>
        <l>vicumpiṭai tūra vāṭi mocintuṭaṉ</l>
        <l>pūvari yakaṉṟuṟaik kaṇaivicaik kaṭunīrk</l>
        <l>kāvirip pēriyāṟ ṟayirkoṇ <supplied>ṭī</supplied>ṇṭi</l>
        <l>yekka riṭṭa kuppai veṇma<supplied>ṇa</supplied>l</l>
        <l>veṟpiṉ yāṇar vaḷaṅkeḻu vēntar</l>
        <l>ñāla nāṟum nalaṅkeḻu nallicai</l>
        <l>nāṉmaṟai mutunūṉ mukkaṭ celva</l>
        <l>ṉāla muṟṟaṅ kaviṉpeṟat taiiyap</l>
        <l>poykai cūḻnta poḻiṉmaṉai makaḷir</l>
        <l>kaicey pāvait tuṟaikka ṇiṟukku</l>
        <l>makara neṟṟi vāṉṟōy puricaic</l>
        <l>cikaran tōṉṟāc cēṇuyar nalliṟ</l>
        <l>pukā<supplied>a</supplied>r naṉṉāṭ ṭatuvē pakarvar</l>
        <l>paṇṭa nāṟum vaṇṭā ṭaimpāṟ</l>
        <l>paṇaittakait taṭai<supplied>iya</supplied> kāṇ<supplied>pi</supplied>ṉ meṉṟō</l>
        <l>ḷaṇaṅkucā larivai yirunta</l>
        <l>maṇaṅkamaḻ maṟukiṉ maṇaṟperuṅ kuṉṟē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>You who cannot resolve [on passing] even the forest difficult to approach, (1)</l>
        <l>if you plan on staying behind [and] returning, (2)</l>
        <l>talk about my state, heart! (3)</l>
        <l>It is in the good land of Pukāar, (22a-c)</l>
        <l>with good houses high from a distance that will not appear over the tops (21)</l>
        <l>of the sky-touching fortifications with makara fronts, (20)</l>
        <l>where in the ghat area stay the dolls made by the hands (19)</l>
        <l>of girls from houses with groves surrounded by ponds (18)</l>
        <l>that have tied [them] beautifully, in Ālamuṟṟam (17)</l>
        <l>of the three-eyed lord of the ancient treatises of the four Vedas, (16)</l>
        <l>of good fame that pervades the world, (15)</l>
        <l>[belonging to] kings prosperous with the fertility of the mountains (14)</l>
        <l>of white sand in heaps that are deposited in dunes, (13)</l>
        <l>gathering together the fine sand of the big river Kāviri, (12)</l>
        <l>[her] water swift with the speed of arrows by the vast ghat lined with flowers, (11)</l>
        <l>as [there] swarm together in play, so that the middle of the sky is full, (10)</l>
        <l>clamouring big multitudes of new birds, (9)</l>
        <l>like one to be enveloped by the form of the bright rays (8)</l>
        <l>of the sun, because the hunter of bounty has fallen (7)</l>
        <l>while the battlefield turns red as with the strength of Muruku (6)</l>
        <l>Miñili of murderous fight driving [his] battle spear, (5)</l>
        <l>with a swelling big army that overcame the fortress protected by the enemies, (3df.)</l>
        <l>– the big hill of sand, [its] streets fragrant with scent, (26)</l>
        <l>where the much tormenting young woman is, (25)</l>
        <l>[her] soft shoulders pleasing to see that are plump, the likeness of bamboo, (24)</l>
        <l>with [her hair in] five parts, in which bees play, fragrant of traders’ goods. (22df.)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
